State is in compliance with victims rights.  
The Court conducts a plea colloquy with the Defendant.
The Defendant pleads no contest to Count 1.
The Court finds the Defendant guilty of Count 1.
Counts 2 and 3 are dismissed and read into Count 1.

Witness B presents a statement to the Court.  
The State gives its sentencing recommendation.
The Defense gives its sentencing recommendation.
The Defendant presents a statement.

Court orders the following:

SENTENCE WITHHELD; 
Consecutive to any other sentence - if revoked.  
(0 days credit - if revoked).

Term of Probation: 12 MONTHS; 
Probation concurrent with Milwaukee case;

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Follow through with any assessments, evaluations, treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent; 
*Maintain full-time employment;
*Mental Heath evaluation and treatment deemed appropriate;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done;
*Anger management counseling.  

COSTS:  $243;
DNA SAMPLE AND SURCHARGE:  $200; 
Defendant to provide DNA sample, if not yet provided, immediately if in custody otherwise within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department.
Apply $250.00 cash bail on deposit and remaining balance to be paid as a condition of probation.
